<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="563" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d563">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115/3230</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRP1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-08">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 8, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.30 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s 7th.<note n="1" xml:id="d563fn1">Not printed.</note> No
                                official answer yet to suggestion that <hi rend="italic">Ogeechee</hi> cargo as whole to be dealt with outside paragraph
                                5, order March 11. Meantime, convincing evidence of American
                                ownership, and especially that ownership passed prior to March 11,
                                if sent to me, may enable me as in two cases already settled, to
                                effect immediate release.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SRP1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>